qid=20080621030426AALoCii	0	qid=20080621030426AALoCii	2008-06-21 10:04:26 +0000	Is it possible to go to sentosa by bus or train & then go back to the city by cable car?	
qid=20080621030426AALoCii_answer_1	1	qid=20080621030426AALoCii	2008-06-21 11:36:43 +0000	best_answer	 By Public Bus : Take a bus and alight along ENTITY_Telok_Blangah_Road.Make your way to the HarbourFront Bus interchange & hop onto the orange Sentosa bus.You may seek assistance from the friendly bus captain to find out where to alight . Bus fares vary . Bus numbers : 65 , 80 , 93 , 188 , 855 , 10 , 30 , 97 , 100 , 131 , 143 , 145 , 166 By MRT : Take the ENTITY_North-East_Line_& alight at the HarbourFront ENTITY_MRT Station.Train fares vary.From there , you may either go to the 3rd level of VivoCity shopping mall , transfer onto the ENTITY_Sentosa_Express or you may follow the signs to the HarbourFront Bus interchange.Hop onto the orange ENTITY_Sentosa bus & you 'll be on your way to ENTITY_Sentosa . By Cable Car : Within Sentosa only Normal Cabin Two-way : S$ 13.90 / Adult ; S$ 8.50 / Child -LRB- 3-12 years old -RRB- One-way : S$ 12.90 / Adult ; S$ 7.50 / Child -LRB- 3-12 years old -RRB- Glass Cabin -LRB- 2-way -RRB- Two-way : S$ 20.00 / Adult ; S$ 13.00 / Child -LRB- 3-12 years old -RRB- -LRB- Prices include island admission -RRB- Return to city : Either by bus , train or taxi .
